    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Block the right countershaft assembly against the case wall and pull the mainshaft assembly to the rear to
            free the pilot from the input shaft pocket (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301974">Figure 74</hotlnk>). Tilt the front of the mainshaft up and lift the assembly from
            the case (inset). Use caution as the reverse gear is free and can fall from the shaft.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301974" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301974" filename="../figg13/G1301974.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 74. Pull Mainshaft Assembly to Rear</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
